  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h2 class="heading">Course Overview</h2>
<h4>If you are ready to take on the challenges of a work placement and are prepared to develop the skills necessary to be successful in the workplace, this course is for you.</h4>
<p>The STEP is a full-time work-based study programme, where you can learn problem solving, teamwork and employability skills. You will also improve your Functional Maths and/or English alongside NCFE Employability and may be able to resit your Maths and/or English GCSEs depending on your previous marks.</p>
<h2>Entry Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>There are no formal qualifications required</li>
<li>You must be 16-18 at the start of your course.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h2 class="heading">What will I study?</h2>
<p>You will be taught skills in the classroom through practical activities and assignments. You will also learn more practical skills while you are on your work placement, and will prepare a portfolio of evidence to document your progress.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></mainContent>
